<p class="govuk-body">Make sure errors follow the <a class="govuk-link" href="https://design-system.service.gov.uk/components/error-message/">guidance about error messages</a> in the GOV.UK Design System and have specific error messages for specific error states.</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="research">Research</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">The recommended code has been tested with screen reader users, assistive technologies, supported browsers and multiple device types. Research showed it:</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>displayed as expected</li>
  <li>worked consistently across different assistive technologies</li>
  <li>helped users know where they were in the service</li>
  <li>did not distract users from their task</li>
</ul>

<p class="govuk-body">We need more research. If you have used the page heading and section heading, get in touch to share your research findings.</p>

<p class="govuk-body"><a class="govuk-link" href="https://github.com/hmrc/design-patterns/issues/149">Discuss the page heading on GitHub</a></p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Changes to this pattern</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">On 31 January 2023, this pattern replaced <a class="govuk-link" href="/hmrc-design-patterns/hmrc-design-patterns-archive/page-heading/"> an older version</a>. This was because the pattern did not work in all cases, like headings as labels and legends.</p>

